<TITLE> Laila strengthens in Bay of Bengal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dial 2000 from your GP mobile for latest news Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)The cyclonic storm Laila over the southwest and adjoining southeast areas of the Bay of Bengal has moved slightly northwest-wards, according to a special bulletin of the Meteorological Department on Wednesday. At 3am, the storm was centred about 1310 km southwest of Chittagong port, 1250 km southwest of Cox's Bazaar port and 1180 km south-southwest of Mongla port. The Met Office advised the maritime ports to hoist 'distant warning signal number two.' All fishing boats and trawlers along the northern part of the Bay and deep sea have been asked to stay close to the coast and proceed with caution until further notice. Vessels have also been advised not to venture into deep sea. It is believed that the depression is likely to intensify further and move in a north-westerly direction. Maximum sustained wind speed within 54 km of the storm centre is about 62 kmph, rising to 88 kmph in gusts or squalls. The sea will remain very rough, the bulletin warned
